*bdf
# Exception: lightweight input BDF bundled with tutorial samples (< 2 MB each).
# Heavy intermediate / colored BDF outputs are kept in the abmptools-sample
# repository (see feedback_artifact_placement).
!sample/hbond/imc_amorphous/input/*.bdf
bkp
ABMPTools.egg-info
abmptools.egg-info
*.egg-info
__pycache__
build
dist
tags
for_abmp
*.swp
.project

# Martini 3 force field files (downloaded separately from cgmartini.nl, not redistributed)
ff/
martini_v300.zip

# gmx grompp default output (created when grompp is run from the repo root)
mdout.mdp

# abmptools.crystal smoke / numeric-reference run artifacts (full logs go to OneDrive)
.smoke_artifacts/

# abmptools.crystal public-molecule pipeline outputs (log, ajf, pdb under
# `sample/crystal/<mol>/out_*/` are regenerable; only `<mol>.cif` /
# `UNK.ajf` / `crystal_layer3.yaml` / `monomer.yaml` and `reference/`
# CSVs go into the repo).
sample/crystal/*/out_*/
sample/crystal/*/*.run.stdout
